<p><a href="https://gasbuddy.com" target=_blank>Gas Buddy</a> is a mobile app that locates cheapest gas stations around you by crowd sourcing the data. It’s very simple and is quite handy. However, its rather unpolished and busy UI challenged me to redesign the app to emphasize its simplicity and ease of use.
</p>

<h2>Search and Listing</h2>
<p>Simply type in your zip code or city. If you have your location services on, tap on Near Me to get started. I never knew the app had Near Me button until I examined it closely (the module with gas pump icon inside is a button, surprise!). Search should be simple and effective. Users shouldn’t have to think about what to do on the search page. Gas Buddy’s simplicity should encourage and guide users.</p>

